# Desktop editor: interactive link styling

In the vault **capture** markdown editor (`NoteMarkdownEditor` / table cell editors under `[data-app-surface='capture']`):

- Any document range that **opens or creates** a vault note via **click**, **Mod-click**, or **Mod-Enter** must use the same **interactive link** presentation as the rest of that affordance: wiki links (`cm-wiki-link` / `cm-wiki-link--resolved` / `cm-wiki-link--unresolved`), relative vault `.md` inline links (`cm-md-rel-link` / `cm-md-rel-link--resolved` / `cm-md-rel-link--unresolved`), and **browser** inline links (`cm-md-external-link` / `cm-md-external-href` for `http` / `https` / `mailto` in [`App.css`](apps/desktop/src/App.css)).
- **Hit testing must match styling:** vault navigation and external link activation must **not** trigger from syntax-only characters (`[[` / `]]` on wiki links; Lezer **`LinkMark`** `[` `]` `(` `)` on inline links). Only positions inside the **styled** inner / label / URL spans may activate.
- Do **not** leave **navigable** label or URL text styled as normal body copy while a sibling segment is the only red underlined “link” (users should not get a hidden click target).
- Markdown **bracket and paren marks** may stay muted like other syntax (see wiki `cm-md-wiki-bracket` pattern).

Authoritative behavior: [`specs/architecture/desktop-editor.md`](specs/architecture/desktop-editor.md) (wiki links, WL-6 relative markdown links, and external browser links).
